description: {"blocks":[{"key":"1l4id","text":"This Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) contains guidance on how to voucher Lepidoptera specimens submitted to the Darwin Tree of Life (DToL) project. guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"64vm7","text":"This Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) outlines in more detail the voucher preparation of specimens within the insect order Lepidoptera. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9il7j","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"a9g5s","text":"Collection and preparation of Lepidoptera specimens for barcoding and full genome sequencing should refer to DToL Taxon Specific Standard Operating Procedure for the Terrestrial and Freshwater Arthropoda Working Group. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":109,"length":108}],"data":{}},{"key":"4plum","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cov53","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":1,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fgke3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"53b7o","text":"This SOP focuses mainly on using wings as the primary voucher for Lepidoptera, although other vouchering methods are mentioned. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2g8cb","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fl2jo","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":2,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"643at","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"92isq","text":"Before vouchering the specimen","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":30},{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":30}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"etcve","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c6ltp","text":"Take a high-quality photograph of the specimen from both ventral and dorsal positions (lateral if possible) ensuring that any key ID features are visible before taking the voucher. This is to aid any identification verification as the specimen will later be dissected. Ensure when storing the image it is labelled with the unique identifier (e.g. QR code, specimen barcode), and if possible, for the physical barcode to be included in the image. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e904j","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"mdtm","text":"Vouchering the specimen ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"UNDERLINE","offset":0,"length":23},{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":24}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2kdsc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9rpuf","text":"Note that the whole specimen must be on dry ice whilst are vouchers are being removed. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fj439","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4usmj","text":"A high quality of care must be taken when removing the wings from Lepidoptera specimens. The specimens are delicate, and the wings (re. the voucher) are liable to break or become damaged if handled incorrectly. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1ksl1","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cuo7v","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":3,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"ksv6","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6i81k","text":"1) Remove each wing (both sets) from the Lepidoptera specimen. These must be gently detached from the base of the wing, to cause minimal damage. Using fine forceps is recommended.   ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6419u","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"aue4","text":"2) For smaller Lepidoptera (such as micromoths) it can be easier to remove the wings after sampling the head/thorax/abdomen of the specimen. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4v2uk","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"emda5","text":"3) Place the wing vouchers within a glassine envelope, ideally 75x55mm (see Figure 1 for guidance). The vouchers should be placed in the left-hand corner of the envelope. Place the physical barcode in the envelope if storing temporarily. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4th0h","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"18jnp","text":"4)
